   420	- `branch` resolves to a SHA unrelated to `trial.commit_sha` (not an
   421	  ancestor either direction) → `NotReadyForIntegration`.
   422	- **`branch` tip is equal to `commit_sha`** → promotion succeeds
   423	  (edge of §2 bullet 2 where the branch hasn't advanced).
   424	- **`branch` tip is a descendant of `commit_sha`** → promotion
   425	  succeeds (§2 "commit_sha resolves to a commit on the branch" is
   426	  satisfied when commit_sha is reachable from branch tip, per plan
   427	  step 3). Asserts the squash tree derives from `commit_sha`, not
   428	  from the branch tip — extra commits on the branch are excluded
   429	  from the squash.
   430	
   431	**Metrics re-validation (§2, §5.1):**
   432	
   433	- A trial with metrics containing a key absent from the experiment's
   434	  `metrics_schema` — seeded directly via store internals (bypassing
   435	  submit-time validation) — raises `NotReadyForIntegration` when
   436	  passed to `integrate`. Assert no ref, no field, no event.
   437	- A trial with metrics of the wrong declared type raises similarly.
   438	- A store constructed without a `metrics_schema` integrates trials
   439	  with arbitrary metrics (no-op validator path).
   440	
   441	**Atomic rollback (§3.4):**
   442	
   443	- Monkey-patch `store.integrate_trial` to raise. Run
   444	  `integrate(trial_id)`. Assert:
   445	  - The `trial/*` ref was deleted (compensating write).
   446	  - The original `store.integrate_trial` exception propagates through
   447	    `Integrator.integrate`.
   448	  - Trial `trial_commit_sha` remains `None`.
   449	  - No `trial.integrated` event appears.
   450	  - The commit object is still in the object DB (orphan; GC will
   451	    clean it). Verified via `repo.commit_exists(sha)` returning True.
   452	- Monkey-patch both `store.integrate_trial` and `repo.delete_ref` to
   453	  raise. Assert `AtomicityViolation` surfaces, wrapping both errors.
   454	
   455	**Commit identity:**
   456	
   457	- Custom `author` / `committer` / `clock` are honored. Commit has
   458	  `commit.gpgsign=false` (inherited from `GitRepo`).
   459	- Default `committer = author` when only `author` is supplied.
   460	
   461	**Multi-parent proposal:**
   462	
   463	- A trial with two `parent_commits` produces a commit with two
   464	  parents in order. (§3.2 supports multi-parent squash.)
   465	
   466	## Verification
   467	
   468	1. `uv sync` resolves the new `eden-contracts` + `eden-storage`
   469	   workspace deps for `eden-git`.
   470	2. `uv run ruff check .` clean.
   471	3. `uv run pyright` clean.
   472	4. `uv run pytest -q` green including new tests.
   473	5. `npx --yes markdownlint-cli2@0.14.0 "**/*.md" ...` clean.
   474	6. `pipx run 'check-jsonschema==0.29.4' ...` clean.
   475	7. CI on PR green.
   476	
   477	## Out of scope for this phase
   478	
   479	- Cross-process atomicity / outbox (Phase 8).
   480	- Remote push to Gitea / GitHub (Phase 10).
   481	- Evaluator identity + artifact-inventory optional fields (§4.3,
   482	  §4.4).
   483	- Work-branch retention policy (§1.3 — deployment concern).
   484	- A wire-protocol surface for the integrator (Phase 8).
   485	
   486	## Known risks
   487	
   488	- **Manifest byte-stability is load-bearing.** The idempotency check
   489	  in step 2 re-derives `build_manifest(trial)` and compares to the
   490	  committed blob. If serialization is not deterministic (insertion
   491	  order, whitespace, trailing newline), a second invocation will
   492	  falsely report corruption. Enforced via `sort_keys=True`,
   493	  `indent=2`, trailing `\n`, and a dedicated byte-stability test.
   494	- **Compensating ref-delete can fail.** In pathological cases (fs
   495	  error during rollback), both writes fail and we surface
   496	  `AtomicityViolation`. This is the operator-intervention state
   497	  (§3.4); tests exercise it and assert the wrapped cause is
   498	  visible.
   499	- **Zero-oid hash-algo.** Inherited from Phase 7a — `GitRepo` queries
   500	  `rev-parse --show-object-format` and caches. Integrator's
   501	  `create_ref` / `delete_ref` calls route through that.
   502	- **Ambient git config.** Inherited from Phase 7a's
   503	  `_sanitized_git_env()` + `commit.gpgsign=false` per invocation;
   504	  extends to every integrator invocation automatically.

